The paper addresses the challenge of developing effective human-robot collaboration systems for logistics and manufacturing applications, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed solution involves using deep convolutional models to learn spatial features from RGB-D camera videos, which is a common approach in computer vision (cs.CV). The goal is to semantically segment the frames into a hierarchy of actions, which involves machine learning techniques such as temporal convolutional networks, falling under the categories of human-computer interaction (cs.HC), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
